{"title_page": "Gold \u2013 20 Super Hits", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Gold \u2013 20 Super Hits\n| type       = greatest hits\n| artist     = [[Boney M.]]\n| cover      = Boney M. - Gold - 20 Super Hits.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = November 1992\n| recorded   = 1975-84\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Euro disco]], [[reggae]], [[R&B]]\n| length     = 75:31\n| label      = MCI/[[Bertelsmann Music Group|BMG]] <small>(EU)</small>\n| producer   = [[Frank Farian]]\n| prev_title = [[Daddy Cool \u2013 Star Collection]]\n| prev_year  = 1991\n| next_title = [[The Most Beautiful Christmas Songs of the World]]\n| next_year  = 1992\n| misc       = {{Extra album cover\n | header  = Alternative cover\n | type    = greatest hits\n | cover   = Boney M. - Gold (Canada).jpg\n | border  =\n | alt     =\n | caption = Canadian Edition.\n}}\n{{Singles\n | name        = Gold \u2013 20 Super Hits\n | type        = greatest hits\n | single1     = [[Mega Mix (Boney M. song)|Mega Mix]]\n | single1date = December 1992\n | single2     = [[Brown Girl in the Ring (song)#1993 Remix|Brown Girl in the Ring (Remix)]]\n | single2date = 1 April 1993\n}}\n}}\n\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1=[[Allmusic]]\n|rev1Score={{Rating|4.5|5}} <ref>{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r350045}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Gold \u2013 20 Super Hits''''' is a [[1992 in music|1992]] [[greatest hits album]] by group [[Boney M.]] Shortly after record label [[PolyGram]] had acquired the rights to the [[ABBA]] back catalogue and had issued the multimillion-selling hits package ''[[ABBA Gold: Greatest Hits|Gold: Greatest Hits]]'', [[Bertelsmann Music Group|BMG]] and producer [[Frank Farian]] followed suit with Boney M.'s ''Gold - 20 Super Hits'' which resulted in their best chart entry in the UK (#14 - see ''[[The Greatest Hits (Boney M. 1993)|The Greatest Hits]]'') and most other European countries since 1980's ''[[The Magic of Boney M. - 20 Golden Hits]]''.\n\nProducer Farian infamously edited most of the tracks and also overdubbed them with synthesized 1990s percussion such as disco hi-hats, sampled tambourines and handclaps specifically for this release. These mixes have since appeared on most Boney M. hit collections issued in the 1990s and 2000s without indication, most notably 2006's ''[[The Magic of Boney M.]]'', which featured nearly all of the tracks that appeared on this release in this form.\n\n''Gold - 20 Super Hits''/''[[The Greatest Hits (Boney M. 1993)|The Greatest Hits]]'' included a new \"Boney M. Megamix\", also issued as a single, which reached #7 in the UK in December 1992 and gave the group their tenth UK Top 10 entry.\n\n== Track listing ==\n#\"[[Rivers of Babylon]]\" (Dowe, McNaughton) - 4:15\n#* 1992 overdub version.\n#\"[[Daddy Cool (Boney M. song)|Daddy Cool]]\" (Farian, Reyam) - 3:26\n#* 1992 overdub version.\n#\"[[Sunny (Bobby Hebb song)|Sunny]]\" (Hebb) - 3:56\n#* 1992 overdub version\n#\"[[Brown Girl in the Ring (song)|Brown Girl in the Ring]]\" (Farian) - 4:00\n#* 1992 overdub version.\n#\"[[Rasputin (song)|Rasputin]]\" (Farian, Jay, Reyam) - 4:24\n#* 1992 overdub edit. Original 7\" mix ( - 4:43) remains unreleased on CD.\n#\"[[Ma Baker]]\" (Farian, Jay, Reyam) - 4:05\n#* 1992 overdub edit.\n#\"[[Hooray! Hooray! It's a Holi-Holiday]]\" (Farian) - 3:55\n#* 1992 overdub version. Original 7\" mix remains unreleased on CD.\n#\"[[Painter Man]]\" (Phillips, Pickette) - 3:16\n#* 1992 overdub version.\n#\"[[Belfast (Boney M. song)|Belfast]]\" (Billybury, Deutscher, Menke) - 3:25\n#* 1992 overdub version.\n#\"[[No Woman No Cry]]\" ([[Bob Marley]]) - 4:20\n#* 1992 overdub edit.\n#\"[[Mary's Boy Child]] / Oh My Lord\" ([[Jester Hairston]], Farian, Jay, Lorin) - 4:01\n#* 1992 overdub edit.\n#\"[[El Lute / Gotta Go Home|Gotta Go Home]]\" (Farian, Huth, Jay) - 2:30\n#* 1992 overdub edit. Original 7\" mix ( - 4:40) remains unreleased on CD.\n#\"Still I'm Sad\" (April, McCarty, Samwell-Smith) - 4:24\n#* 1992 overdub edit.\n#\"Nightflight To Venus\" (Farian, Jay, Kawohl) - 3:49\n#* 1992 edited version.\n#\"[[Felicidad (Margherita)]]\" (Conz, Massara) - 2:50\n#* 1992 overdub edit.\n#\"[[El Lute / Gotta Go Home|El Lute]]\" (Blum, Farian, Jay) - 3:58\n#* 1989 remix version from ''[[Greatest Hits Of All Times - Remix '89 - Volume II]]'', edited\n#\"[[Baby Do You Wanna Bump]]\" (Zambi) - 2:25\n#* 1992 overdub edit.\n#\"Kalimba De Luna\" (Amoruso, Esposito, Licastro, Malavasi) - 4:11\n#* 1992 overdub edit.\n#\"Happy Song\" (Abacab, Bacciocci, Spagna) - 3:56\n#* Edited 7\" version.\n#\"Boney M. Megamix\"  (Farian, Reyam, Hebb, Jay) - 3:51\n#* 1992 version, radio edit. (\"[[Rivers of Babylon]]\" / \"[[Sunny (Bobby Hebb song)|Sunny]]\" / \"Daddy Cool\" / \"[[Ma Baker]]\" / \"[[Rasputin (song)|Rasputin]]\")\n\n==Personnel==\n* [[Liz Mitchell]] - [[lead vocals]], [[backing vocals]]\n* [[Marcia Barrett]] - lead vocals, backing vocals\n* [[Frank Farian]] - lead vocals, backing vocals\n* [[Reggie Tsiboe]] - lead vocals, backing vocals (tracks 18 & 19)\n* [[Bobby Farrell]] - vocals (track 19)\n\n== Production==\n* [[Frank Farian]] - [[Record producer|producer]], [[remixer]]\n\n==Release history==\n* 1993 EU: MCI / BMG 74321 12577 1 (LP)\n* 1993 EU: MCI / BMG 74321 12577 2 (CD)\n* 1993 EU: BMG Ariola 74321 126052 7 (CD)\n\n==Single releases==\n'''EU'''\n\n7\"\n\n* \"Megamix\" (Radio Edit) -3:51 / \"Bang Bang Lulu\" - 3:01 (MCI/[[Bertelsmann Music Group|BMG]] 74321 12606-7, 1992)\n<br />\n12\"\n\n* \"Megamix\" (MCI/BMG 74321 12606-1, 1992)\nSide A\n# \"Megamix (Long Version) - 6:12\n# \"Babysitter\" (1983 recording - 1992 remix) - 3:48\nSide B\n# \"Megamix\" (Radio edit) - 3:51\n# \"Bang Bang Lulu\" - 3:01\n\n* \"Brown Girl In The Ring (Remix '93)\" (MCI/BMG 74321 13705 1, 1993)\nSide A\n# \"Brown Girl in the Ring\" (Funny Girl Club Mix) - 5:35\n# \"The Calendar Song (January, February, March...)\" (Remix '93) - 3:14\nSide B\n# \"Brown Girl in the Ring\" (Club Mix - Rap Version) - 5:35\n# \"Brown Girl in the Ring\" (Radio Version) 