, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Spanish Albums ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|PROMUSICAE]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/4170-%C3%81lbumes-semana-37-2019 |title=Top 100 Albumes \u2013 Semana 37: del 6 September 2019 al 12.9.2019 |publisher=[[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a]] |language=Spanish |accessdate=September 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| 15\n|-\n{{album chart|Switzerland|16|artist=Soundtrack|album=Quentin Tarantino's Once Upon a Time in Hollywood|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 28, 2019}}\n|}\n\n=== Additional music ===\nOther songs in the film include \"[[The Letter (Box Tops song)|The Letter]]\" by [[Joe Cocker]], \"[[Summertime (George Gershwin song)|Summertime]]\" by [[Billy Stewart]], \"Victorville Blues\" by The Harley Hatcher Combo, \"Ready for Action\" by [[Syd Dale]], \"[[Funky Fanfare]]\" by [[Keith Mansfield]], \"[[The House That Jack Built (song)|The House That Jack Built]]\" by [[Aretha Franklin]], \"Time for Livin'\" by [[The Association]], \"[[I Can't Turn You Loose]]\" by [[Otis Redding]], \"[[Soul Serenade (King Curtis song)|Soul Serenade]]\" by [[Willie Mitchell (musician)|Willie Mitchell]], \"[[Out of Time (The Rolling Stones song)|Out of Time]]\" by [[the Rolling Stones]], \"[[Twelve Thirty (Young Girls Are Coming to the Canyon)]]\" by [[the Mamas and the Papas]], \"[[Snoopy vs. the Red Baron (song)|Snoopy vs. the Red Baron]]\" by [[The Royal Guardsmen]], \"Straight Shooter\" by the Mamas and the Papas, also performed by [[Samantha Robinson (American actress)|Samantha Robinson]] as [[Abigail Folger]], and \"[[The Green Door]]\" performed by [[Leonardo DiCaprio]] as Rick Dalton.<ref name=every-song>{{cite news |last=Moran |first=Sarah |url=https://screenrant.com/once-upon-time-hollywood-movie-soundtrack-songs/ |title=Every Song in Once Upon a Time in Hollywood |website=[[Screen Rant]] |access-date=August 25, 2019 |date=July 26, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190727133005/https://screenrant.com/once-upon-time-hollywood-movie-soundtrack-songs/ |archive-date=July 27, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=soundtrack/>\n\nMusic by [[Bernard Herrmann]] created for ''[[Torn Curtain]]'' is used in the Spahn Ranch scene.<ref>{{cite web |last=Chow |first=Andrew R. |url=https://time.com/5637336/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-soundtrack/ |title=Breaking Down the Hidden Meanings and Historical References in the Once Upon a Time... in Hollywood Soundtrack |website=Time |access-date=September 2, 2019 |date=July 29, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190731021716/https://time.com/5637336/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-soundtrack/ |archive-date=July 31, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Herrman's music from that film included in ''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood'' is \"The Killing\", and \"The Radiogram\". Other music of his used is \"The Rocks\", and \"The Return\" (from ''[[Have Gun Will Travel]]''). Also used are the themes from ''[[Hell River]]'' by Vojislav Borisavljevic, ''[[Against a Crooked Sky]]'' by Alexis de Azevedo, ''[[:it: Un uomo chiamato Apocalisse Joe|Apocalypse Joe]]'' by [[Bruno Nicolai]], and ''[[Mannix]]'' by [[Lalo Schifrin]]. Also, \"Paxton Quigley's Had the Course\" (from ''[[Three in the Attic]]''), \"The Bed\" by [[Ennio Morricone]] (from ''[[Danger: Diabolik]]''), \"Ecce Homo\" (from ''[[:it: Sartana non perdona|Sartana Does Not Forgive]]'') and \"Mexican Western\" (from ''[[Any Gun Can Play]]'') by [[Francesco De Masi]], \"Cooler\" by [[Elmer Bernstein]] (from ''[[The Great Escape (film)|The Great Escape]]''), \"Freya Bangs\", \"Freya\", \"Karate Dance\", and \"TV Screen\" (from ''[[The Wrecking Crew (1968 film)|The Wrecking Crew]]''), \"Theme from ''[[It's Happening]]''\" by [[Paul Revere & the Raiders]], \"Dalton Gang Ride Entrance\" performed by Tom Slocum, John Bird, and the Cattle Annie Band (from ''[[Cattle Annie and Little Britches]]''), the \"Batman Theme\" (from ''[[Batman (TV series)|Batman]])'', the \"FBI Theme and Score Cues\" (from ''[[The F.B.I. (TV series)|The F.B.I.]]''), and \"Miss Lilly Langtry\" and \"Judge Roy Bean's Theme\" by [[Maurice Jarre]] (from ''[[The Life and Times of Judge Roy Bean]]'').<ref name=soundtrack>{{cite web |last=Gorber |first=Jason |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-soundtrack-deep-dive/3/ |title=How the 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' Soundtrack Helps Quentin Tarantino Shape His Version of 1969 Los Angeles |website=[[/Film]] |access-date=September 4, 2019 |date=August 1, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190802231046/https://www.slashfilm.com/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-soundtrack-deep-dive/3/ |archive-date=August 2, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n[[File:Tarantino and Robbie at 2019 Cannes (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright=0.8|Tarantino and Robbie at the [[2019 Cannes Film Festival]]]]\n''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood'' premiered at the [[Cannes Film Festival]] on May 21, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-cannes-competition-quentin-tarantino-1203201142/ |title='Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' Joins Cannes' Competition Roster |date=May 2, 2019 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=May 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502132152/https://variety.com/2019/film/news/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-cannes-competition-quentin-tarantino-1203201142/|archive-date=May 2, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.festival-cannes.com/en/press/press-articles/communique/articles/the-screenings-guide-2019 |title=The Screenings Guide 2019 |date=May 9, 2019 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=May 9, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190509101313/https://www.festival-cannes.com/en/press/press-articles/communique/articles/the-screenings-guide-2019|archive-date=May 9, 2019}}</ref> It was released theatrically in the United States on July 26, 2019 by [[Sony Pictures Releasing]] under its [[Columbia Pictures]] label.<ref>{{cite web |last1=McClintock |first1=Pamela |title=Quentin Tarantino's Manson Movie Shifts Off Sharon Tate Murder Anniversary Date |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/quentin-tarantinos-manson-movie-will-hit-theaters-two-weeks-early-1128206 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=July 18, 2018 |date=July 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180719024659/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/quentin-tarantinos-manson-movie-will-hit-theaters-two-weeks-early-1128206|archive-date=July 19, 2018}}</ref> The film was originally scheduled for release on August 9 to coincide with the 50th anniversary of the [[Tate\u2013LaBianca murders]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/sony-dates-quentin-tarantinos-9-for-1202218496/ |title=Quentin Tarantino's Manson Movie Set For Release on 50th Anniversary of Sharon Tate's Death |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |date=December 1, 2017 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=June 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618175501/https://deadline.com/2017/12/sony-dates-quentin-tarantinos-9-for-1202218496/|archive-date=June 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\nA [[teaser campaign|teaser trailer]] was released on March 20, 2019, featuring 1960s music by [[the Mamas and the Papas]] (\"Straight Shooter\") and by [[Los Bravos]] (\"[[Bring a Little Lovin']]\").<ref>{{cite news |last1=Singer |first1=Matt |title=What Are the Songs in the Once Upon a Time in Hollywood Trailer? |url=https://screencrush.com/what-are-the-songs-in-the-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-trailer/ |accessdate=March 21, 2019 |website=[[Townsquare Media#Web publications and services|ScreenCrush]] |date=March 20, 2019 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190321175233/https://screencrush.com/what-are-the-songs-in-the-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-trailer/ |archive-date=March 21, 2019}}</ref> The official trailer was released on May 21, 2019 featuring the songs \"[[Good Thing (Paul Revere & The Raiders song)|Good Thing]]\" by [[Paul Revere & the Raiders]], and \"[[Brother Love's Travelling Salvation Show (song)|Brother Love's Travelling Salvation Show]]\" by [[Neil Diamond]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tunefind.com/movie/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-2019 |title=Songs and music featured in Once Upon a Time in Hollywood |last= |first= |date=July 2019 |website=[[Tunefind]] |access-date= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724142756/https://www.tunefind.com/movie/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-2019 |archive-date=July 24, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> The studio spent around $110 million marketing the film.<ref name=opening/>\n\nAn extended cut of the film featuring four additional scenes was released in theaters on October 25, 2019.<ref name=extended-cut>{{cite news| url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-news/quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-rerelease-new-footage-902715/| title=Quentin Tarantino Re-Releasing \"Once Upon a Time in Hollywood\" With Unseen Footage| last=Reed| first=Ryan| website=RollingStone| access-date=October 24, 2019| date=October 23, 2019| url-status=live| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024011955/https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-news/quentin-tarantino-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-rerelease-new-footage-902715/| archive-date=October 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Home media ===\nThe film was released on digital and [[Movies Anywhere]] on November 22, 2019, and on [[Blu-ray]], [[Ultra HD Blu-ray|4K Ultra HD]], and [[DVD-Video|DVD]] on December 10. The 4K version is available as a regular version and collector's edition.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Evangelista |first1=Chris |title='Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' Blu-ray Releasing in December With Special Collector's Edition |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-blu-ray/ |accessdate=October 28, 2019 |work=[[/Film]] |date=October 28, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029003843/https://www.slashfilm.com/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-blu-ray/ |archive-date=October 29, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Box office ===\n{{As of|2020|2|13|df=US}}, ''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood'' has grossed $142.5 million in the United States and Canada, and $231.8 million in other territories, for a worldwide total of $374.3 million.<ref name=\"BOM\"/> By some estimates, the film needed to gross around $250 million worldwide in order to [[break-even]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Lee |first=Chris |url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/08/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-box-office-bet-pays-off.html |title=The Bet on ''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood'' Is Paying Off |website=[[New York (magazine)#Digital expansion and blogs|Vulture]] |access-date=September 6, 2019 |date=August 5, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190805145753/https://www.vulture.com/2019/08/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-box-office-bet-pays-off.html |archive-date=August 5, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> with others estimating it would need to make $400 million in order to turn a profit.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/once-a-time-hollywood-debut-doesnt-guarantee-a-happy-ending-1227512 |title=Box Office: Why 'Once Upon a Time in Hollywood's' $40M Debut Doesn't Guarantee a Fairy Tale Ending |date=July 29, 2019 |first=Pamela|last= McClintock |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=August 28, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190809094907/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/once-a-time-hollywood-debut-doesnt-guarantee-a-happy-ending-1227512 |archive-date=August 9, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn the United States and Canada, the film was projected to gross $30\u201340 million from 3,659 theaters in its opening weekend, with some projections having it as high as $50 million or as low as $25 million.<ref name=EarlyProjections>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/quentin-tarantinos-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-eyes-30m-opening-1202641601/ |title=Quentin Tarantino's 'Once Upon A Time In Hollywood' Eyes $30M Opening |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=July 3, 2019 |access-date=July 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703161646/https://deadline.com/2019/07/quentin-tarantinos-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-eyes-30m-opening-1202641601/ |archive-date=July 3, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thewrap.com/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-box-office/ |title=Once Upon a Time in Hollywood': Will Sony's Bet on Quentin Tarantino Pay Off? |last=Fuster |first=Jeremy |website=[[TheWrap]] |date=July 23, 2019 |access-date=July 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724035722/https://www.thewrap.com/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-box-office/ |archive-date=July 24, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> The week of its release, [[Fandango (company)|Fandango]] reported the film was the highest pre-seller of any Tarantino film.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-biggest-fandango-preseller-1202652829/ |title='Once Upon A Time In Hollywood' Is Quentin Tarantino's Biggest Preseller On Fandango |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=July 24, 2019 |access-date=July 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724202322/https://deadline.com/2019/07/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-biggest-fandango-preseller-1202652829/ |archive-date=July 24, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> The film made $16.9 million on its first day, including $5.8 million from Thursday night previews (the highest total of Tarantino's career). It went on to debut to $41.1 million, finishing second behind holdover ''[[The Lion King (2019 film)|The Lion King]]'' and marking Tarantino's largest opening. [[Comscore]] reported that 47% of audience members went to see the film because of who the director was (compared to the typical 7%) and 37% went because of the cast (compared to normally 18%).<ref name=opening>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-box-office-lion-king-weekend-1202654606/ |title=Hooray For 'Hollywood': Quentin Tarantino Sees His Biggest B.O. Opening Of All-Time With $40M+ As 'Lion King' Still Lords With $76M+ \u2013 Sunday Update |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=July 27, 2019 |access-date=July 27, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726232213/https://deadline.com/2019/07/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-box-office-lion-king-weekend-1202654606/ |archive-date=July 26, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> The film grossed $20 million in its second weekend, representing a \"nice\" drop of just 51% and finishing third, and then made $11.6 million and $7.6 million the subsequent weekends.<ref>{{cite news |last1=D'Alessandro |first1=Anthony |title='Hobbs & Shaw' West Coast Business Driving Pic To $60M, But Looks To Overseas For More Muscle |url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/hobbs-shaw-targeting-4-5m-thursday-night-early-b-o-read-1202659422/ |accessdate=August 4, 2019 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=August 4, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190803004918/https://deadline.com/2019/08/hobbs-shaw-targeting-4-5m-thursday-night-early-b-o-read-1202659422/ |archive-date=August 3, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/dora-and-the-lost-city-of-gold-hobbs-shaw-the-kitchen-box-office-weekend-1202665153/ |title='Hobbs' Hauls $25M; 'Scary Stories' Frighten 'Dora'; 'Kitchen' Sinks Melissa McCarthy & Tiffany Haddish To Career B.O. Lows \u2013 Saturday AM Update |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=August 11, 2019 |access-date=August 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190810145835/https://deadline.com/2019/08/dora-and-the-lost-city-of-gold-hobbs-shaw-the-kitchen-box-office-weekend-1202665153/ |archive-date=August 10, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/good-boys-hobbs-shaw-47-meters-down-uncaged-scary-stories-weekend-box-office-1202669605/ |title=How Universal Is Reviving The R-Rated Comedy & Making 'Good Boys' Great At The B.O. With A $21M Opening |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=August 18, 2019 |access-date=August 18, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816181043/https://deadline.com/2019/08/good-boys-hobbs-shaw-47-meters-down-uncaged-scary-stories-weekend-box-office-1202669605/ |archive-date=August 16, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> In its fourth weekend the film made $5 million, bringing its running domestic total to $123.1 million, becoming the second-highest of Tarantino's career behind ''[[Django Unchained]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/ready-or-not-angel-has-fallen-good-boys-box-office-weekend-1202701545/ |title='Angel Has Fallen' Still Ascending Close To 'London' With $20M; Tarantino's 'Hollywood' Beating 'Basterds' \u2013 Saturday AM B.O. |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=August 25, 2019 |access-date=August 28, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822231242/https://deadline.com/2019/08/ready-or-not-angel-has-fallen-good-boys-box-office-weekend-1202701545/ |archive-date=August 22, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> In its ninth weekend, its global total earnings reached $329.4 million, surpassing ''[[Inglourious Basterds]]'' to become Tarantino's second-highest global grosser behind ''Django Unchained''.<ref>{{cite news |last=Mendelson |first=Scott |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2019/09/15/box-office-quentin-tarantino-leonardo-dicaprio-brad-pitt-margot-robbie-dwayne-johnson-jason-statham-john-wick-keanu-reeves-peanut-butter-falcon-shia-labeouf-dakota-johnson-farwell-awkwafina-lion-king-rogue-one-dark-knight/ |title=Box Office: 'Hollywood' Tops 'Basterds' As 'Lion King' Nears 'Dark Knight' And 'Hobbs & Shaw' Nears 'John Wick 3' |website=[[Forbes]] |access-date=September 15, 2019 |date=September 15, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190916044551/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2019/09/15/box-office-quentin-tarantino-leonardo-dicaprio-brad-pitt-margot-robbie-dwayne-johnson-jason-statham-john-wick-keanu-reeves-peanut-butter-falcon-shia-labeouf-dakota-johnson-farwell-awkwafina-lion-king-rogue-one-dark-knight/ |archive-date=September 16, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical response ===\nOn [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 85% based on 515 reviews, with an [[Weighted arithmetic mean|average rating]] of 7.83/10. The site's critical consensus reads, \"Thrillingly unrestrained yet solidly crafted, ''Once Upon a Time in Hollywood'' tempers Tarantino's provocative impulses with the clarity of a mature filmmaker's vision.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/once_upon_a_time_in_hollywood |title=Once Upon a Time in Hollywood (2019) |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=December 12, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330050307/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/once_upon_a_time_in_hollywood |archive-date=March 30, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Metacritic]] assigned the film a [[weighted average]] score of 83 out of 100, based on 61 critics, indicating \"universal acclaim.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood |title=Once Upon a Time in Hollywood Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=September 28, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722083158/https://www.metacritic.com/movie/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood |archive-date=July 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave it an average grade of \"B\" on an A+ to F scale, while those at [[PostTrak]] gave it an average of 4 out of 5 stars and a 58% \"definite recommend.\"<ref name=\"opening\"/>\n\n''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' said critics had \"an overall positive view,\" with some calling it \"Tarantino's love letter to '60s L.A.,\" praising its cast and setting, while others were \"divided on its ending.\"<ref name=\"beresford\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/once-a-time-hollywood-reviews-what-critics-are-saying-1212670 |first1=Trilby |last1=Beresford |first2=Katie |last2=Kilkenny |title='Once Upon a Time in Hollywood': What the Critics Are Saying |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=May 21, 2019 |accessdate=May 21, 2019}}</ref> ReelViews' [[James Berardinelli]] awarded the film 3.5 stars out of 4, saying it was \"made by a movie-lover for movie-lovers. And even those who don't qualify may still enjoy the hell out of it.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.reelviews.net/reelviews/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood |title=Once Upon a Time in Hollywood (United States, 2019) |first=James |last=Berardinelli |website=reelviews.com |date=July 24, 2019 |access-date=August 18, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818104043/http://www.reelviews.net/reelviews/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood |archive-date=August 18, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[RogerEbert.com]]'s Brian Tallerico gave it four out of four stars, calling it \"layered and ambitious, the product of a confident filmmaker working with collaborators completely in tune with his vision\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/once-upon-a-time-in--hollywood-2019 |title=Once Upon a Time ... in Hollywood Movie Review (2019) |last=Tallerico |first=Brian |work=[[RogerEbert.com]] |date=July 23, 2019 |accessdate=August 19, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190814182022/https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/once-upon-a-time-in--hollywood-2019 |archive-date=August 14, 2019 |url-status=live}} {{Rating|4|4}}</ref> The ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'', [[Richard Roeper]] described it as \"a brilliant and sometimes outrageously fantastic mash-up of real-life events and characters with pure fiction,\" giving it full marks.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://chicago.suntimes.com/2019/7/22/20706094/once-upon-time-hollywood-review-movie-quentin-tarantino-brad-pitt-leonardo-dicaprio-richard-roeper |title='Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' review: Quentin Tarantino's colorful snapshot of an era |first=Richard |last=Roeper |author-link=Richard Roeper |work=[[Chicago Sun-Times]] |date=July 22, 2019 |accessdate=September 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190904035133/https://chicago.suntimes.com/2019/7/22/20706094/once-upon-time-hollywood-review-movie-quentin-tarantino-brad-pitt-leonardo-dicaprio-richard-roeper |archive-date=September 4, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Writing for ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', [[Owen Gleiberman]] called it a \"heady engrossing collage of a film\u2014but not, in the end, a masterpiece.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/reviews/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-review-quentin-tarantino-brad-pitt-leonardo-dicaprio-cannes-film-1203222012/ |title=Cannes Film Review: 'Once Upon a Time...in Hollywood' |first=Owen |last=Gleiberman |date=May 21, 2019 |access-date=July 4, 2019 |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |publisher=[[Penske Business Media, LLC.]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190614092258/https://variety.com/2019/film/reviews/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-review-quentin-tarantino-brad-pitt-leonardo-dicaprio-cannes-film-1203222012/ |archive-date=June 14, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Peter Bradshaw]] of ''[[The Guardian]]'' gave it five out of five stars, praising Pitt and DiCaprio's performances and calling it \"Tarantino's dazzling LA redemption song.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/may/21/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-review-tarantino-dazzling-dicaprio-pitt |title=Once Upon a Time ... in Hollywood review \u2013 Tarantino's dazzling LA redemption song |first=Peter |last=Bradshaw |website=[[The Guardian]] |date=May 21, 2019 |accessdate=July 4, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703222104/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/may/21/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-review-tarantino-dazzling-dicaprio-pitt |archive-date=July 3, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Steve Pond of ''[[TheWrap]]'' said: \"Big, brash, ridiculous, too long, and in the end invigorating, the film is a grand playground for its director to fetishize old pop culture and bring his gleeful perversity to the craft of moviemaking.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thewrap.com/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-film-review-a-contemplative-quentin-tarantino-still-blows-the-roof-off-cannes/ |title='Once Upon a Time ... in Hollywood' Film Review: A Contemplative Quentin Tarantino Still Blows the Roof Off Cannes |last=Pond |first=Steve |website=[[TheWrap]] |date=May 21, 2019 |accessdate=July 4, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190704173107/https://www.thewrap.com/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-film-review-a-contemplative-quentin-tarantino-still-blows-the-roof-off-cannes/ |archive-date=July 4, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Peter Travers]] of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' awarded the film 4.5 out of 5 stars, remarking that \"All the actors, in roles large and small, bring their A games to the film. Two hours and 40 minutes can feel long for some. I wouldn't change a frame.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-reviews/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-movie-review-quentin-tarantino-861778/ |title='Once Upon a Time in Hollywood' Review: Tarantino's Violent Tinseltown Valentine |authorlink=Peter Travers |last=Travers |first=Peter |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=July 22, 2019 |accessdate=September 10, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190907183059/https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-reviews/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-movie-review-quentin-tarantino-861778/ |archive-date=September 7, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nKatie Rife of ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' gave it a B+, calling it Tarantino's \"wistful midlife crisis movie.\"<ref name=\"avc\">{{Cite web |url=https://film.avclub.com/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-is-quentin-tarantino-s-1836636382 |title='Once Upon a Time...In Hollywood' Is Quentin Tarantino's Wistful Midlife Crisis Movie |last=Rife |first=Katie |date=July 24, 2019 |accessdate=July 24, 2019 |website=[[The A.V. Club]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724151612/https://film.avclub.com/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-is-quentin-tarantino-s-1836636382 |archive-date=July 24, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Richard Brody]] of ''[[The New Yorker]]'' called it an \"obscenely regressive vision of the sixties\" that \"celebrates white-male stardom (and behind-the-scenes command) at the expense of everyone else.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.newyorker.com/culture/the-front-row/review-quentin-tarantinos-obscenely-regressive-vision-of-the-sixties-in-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood |title=Review: Quentin Tarantino's Obscenely Regressive Vision of the Sixties in 'Once Upon a Time . . . in Hollywood' |last=Brody |first=Richard |date=July 27, 2019 |website=[[The New Yorker]] |access-date=August 17, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816141803/https://www.newyorker.com/culture/the-front-row/review-quentin-tarantinos-obscenely-regressive-vision-of-the-sixties-in-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood |archive-date=August 16, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> In [[Little White Lies (magazine)|''Little White Lies'']], [[Christopher Hooton]] described it as \"occasionally tedious\" but \"constantly awe-inspiring,\" noting it did not seem to be a \"love letter to Hollywood\" but an \"obituary for a moment in culture that looks unlikely to ever be resurrected.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://lwlies.com/articles/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-love-letter-obituary/ |title=Once Upon a Time in Hollywood isn't a love letter, it's an obituary |last=Hooton |first=Christopher |date=August 26, 2019 |website=[[Little White Lies (magazine)|Little White Lies]] |access-date= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190826112553/https://lwlies.com/articles/once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood-quentin-tarantino-love-letter-obituary/ |archive-date=August 26, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe film also garnered moral and theological praise. The Los Angeles Catholic Bishop [[Robert Barron]] praised the character of Cliff Booth as embodying the four [[cardinal virtues]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.wordonfire.org/resources/video/bishop-barron-on-once-upon-a-time-in-hollywood/24840/|title=Bishop Barron on \u201cOnce Upon A Time In Hollywood\u201d |last=Barron |first=Robert |date=August 8, 2019 |website=Wordonfire.org}}</ref> while the theologian [[David Bentley Hart]] wrote that the film \"exhibit[s] a genuine ethical pathos, one that actually brought tears to my eyes\" for its portrayal of \"cosmic justice.\" Specifically, Hart praised the revisionism when \"Tarantino's version of the story unexpectedly veered away into some other, dreamlike, better world, where the monsters inadvertently passed through the wrong door and met the end they deserved\" that \"gave glorious expression to a perfectly righteous rage\" in \"some other order of reality, if only an imaginary one, where ethereal sweetness had survived and horror had perished.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/06/opinion/quentin-tarantino.html|title=Quentin Tarantino's Cosmic Justice|last=Hart |first=David Bentley |date=August 6, 2019 |website=[[New York Times]]}}</ref>\n\n=== Accolades ===\n{{Main|List of accolades received by Once Upon a Time in Hollywood}}\nThe film premiered at the [[2019 Cannes Film Festival]] where it won the [[Palm Dog Award]] and was nominated for the [[Palme d'Or]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Sharf |first=Zack |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/05/2019-cannes-winners-palme-dor-1202144785/ |title=Cannes 2019 Full Winners List: Bong Joon-ho Wins Palme d'Or for \"Parasite\" |website=indiewire |access-date=September 1, 2019 |date=May 25, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190604171148/https://www.indiewire.com/2019/05/2019-cannes-winners-palme-dor-1202144785/ |archive-date=June 4, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Utichi |first=Joe |url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/quentin-tarantino-wins-palm-dog-award-cannes-1202621869/ |title=Quentin Tarantino Accepts Palm Dog Award For Best Cannes Canine Performance In 'Once Upon A Time In Hollywood' |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=May 24, 2019 |access-date=August 20, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823203020/https://deadline.com/2019/05/quentin-tarantino-wins-palm-dog-award-cannes-1202621869/ |archive-date=August 23, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> The film received 10 nominations at the [[92nd Academy Awards]], including [[Academy Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]], [[Academy Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]], [[Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]], and [[Academy Award for Best Director|Best Director]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/academy-awards-oscar-nominations-2020-full-list|title=Oscar Nominations Are Here, and Yes, There Are Snubs|last=Grebey|first=James|website=[[GQ]]|language=en|access-date=2020-01-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200113190408/https://www.gq.com/story/academy-awards-oscar-nominations-2020-full-list|archive-date=January 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> It received five nominations at the [[77th Golden Globe Awards]], winning for [[Golden Globe Award for Best Motion Picture \u2013 Musical or Comedy|Best Motion Picture \u2013 Musical or Comedy]], [[Golden Globe Award for Best Screenplay|Best Screenplay]] for Quentin Tarantino, and [[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Motion Picture|Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Motion Picture]] for Brad Pitt.<ref name=\"GoldenGlobeAwards\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/2020-golden-globes-nominations-list-nominees-1203426905/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209155146/https://variety.com/2019/film/news/2020-golden-globes-nominations-list-nominees-1203426905/ |title=Golden Globes 2020: The Complete Nominations List |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=December 9, 2019 |accessdate=December 9, 2019 |archivedate=December 9, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/golden-globes-winners-2020-list-best-actor-actress-picture-awards-a9271126.html|title=Golden Globes 2020 winners: The full list|last=Stolworthy|first=Jacob|website=[[The Independent]]|date=January 6, 2020|accessdate=January 6, 2020}}</ref> It received twelve nominations at the [[25th Critics' Choice Awards]], including [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]], [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Director|Best Director]] for Tarantino, [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] for Leonardo DiCaprio, and [[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]] for Pitt.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/12/critics-choice-nominations-film-tv-nominees-list-1202803785/|title='The Irishman', 'Once Upon A Time In Hollywood' Lead Critics' Choice Nominations; Netflix Dominates With 61 Noms in Movies And TV|first1=Pete|last1=Hammond|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=December 8, 2019|access-date=December 9, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191208185645/https://deadline.com/2019/12/critics-choice-nominations-film-tv-nominees-list-1202803785/|archive-date=December 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> DiCaprio and Pitt also received nominations at the [[26th Screen Actors Guild Awards]] where it was also nominated for [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture|Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture]] and [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Stunt Ensemble in a Motion Picture|Outstanding Performance by a Stunt Ensemble in a Motion Picture]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sagawards.org/media/news/releases/nominations-announced-26th-annual-screen-actors-guild-awards-%C2%AE |publisher=[[Screen Actors Guild Awards]]|title=NOMINATIONS ANNOUNCED FOR THE 26TH ANNUAL SCREEN ACTORS GUILD AWARDS |date=December 11, 2019 |accessdate=December 11, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191212024926/https://www.sagawards.org/media/news/releases/nominations-announced-26th-annual-screen-actors-guild-awards-%C2%AE |archive-date=December 12, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The [[National Board of Review]] included the film as one of the [[National Board of Review Awards 2019#Top 10 Films|top 10 films of the year]] and awarded Tarantino [[National Board of Review Award for Best Director|Best Director]] and Pitt [[National Board of Review Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2019/12/national-board-of-review-2019-winners-irishman-1202193897/|title=National Board of Review 2019: 'The Irishman' Wins Best Film, Adam Sandler Named Best Actor|publisher=[[IndieWire]]|first1=Zack|last1=Sharf|first2=Zack|last2=Sharf|date=December 3, 2019|access-date=December 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203194830/https://www.indiewire.com/2019/12/national-board-of-review-2019-winners-irishman-1202193897/|archive-date=December 3, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[American Film Institute]] included it as one of the [[American Film Institute Awards 2019#Top 10 Films|top 10 films of 2019]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nextbestpicture.com/latest/the-afi-top-10-films-of-2019/|title=The AFI Top 10 Films of 2019|first1=Matt|last1=Neglia|publisher=[[American Film Institute]]|date=December 4, 2019|access-date=December 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191204233746/https://www.nextbestpicture.com/latest/the-afi-top-10-films-of-2019|archive-date=December 4, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==